Spain Opposition Party Wants Airport Contracts Delay, Cinco Says

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-09-16T06:28:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/spain-opposition-party-wants-airport-contracts-delay-cinco-says.html
Spain ’s opposition  People’s Party 
will call for the awarding of contracts to manage Madrid and
Barcelona airports and air traffic control towers to be
postponed until elections due on Nov. 20,  Cinco Dias  reported,
citing people it didn’t name with knowledge of the matter.  Andres Ayala, the party’s transport spokesman, held talks
with his superiors and it was decided they will demand that the
government delay the selection until after elections on Nov. 20,
the newspaper said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at   ablackman@bloomberg.net  